ScanSource, Inc. (SCSC) Shares Bought by KCG Holdings Inc.

					Posted by Andrew Steele on Jul 24th, 2017 // No Comments 



KCG Holdings Inc. raised its stake in shares of  ScanSource, Inc. (NASDAQ:SCSC) by 57.1% during the first quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the SEC. The institutional investor  owned 7,938 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after buying an additional 2,886 shares during the period. KCG Holdings Inc.’s holdings in ScanSource were worth $312,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Several other institutional investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in SCSC. SG Americas Securities LLC boosted its position in shares of  ScanSource by 0.3% in the first quarter. SG Americas Securities LLC now owns 4,259 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $167,000 after buying an additional 14 shares during the period.  State of Alaska Department of Revenue boosted its position in shares of  ScanSource by 0.7% in the first quarter. State of Alaska Department of Revenue now owns 2,790 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $109,000 after buying an additional 20 shares during the period.  Louisiana State Employees Retirement System boosted its position in shares of  ScanSource by 2.0% in the first quarter. Louisiana State Employees Retirement System now owns 10,300 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $404,000 after buying an additional 200 shares during the period.  Arizona State Retirement System boosted its position in shares of  ScanSource by 1.5% in the first quarter. Arizona State Retirement System now owns 13,182 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $517,000 after buying an additional 200 shares during the period.  Finally, Blair William & Co. IL boosted its position in shares of  ScanSource by 3.8% in the first quarter. Blair William & Co. IL now owns 6,858 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $269,000 after buying an additional 250 shares during the period. Institutional investors own  94.44% of the company’s stock. 


 Get ScanSource Inc. alerts:



ScanSource, Inc. (NASDAQ:SCSC) opened at 40.80 on Monday. ScanSource, Inc. has a 52 week low of $29.05 and a 52 week high of $44.95. The company’s 50-day moving average price is $39.53 and its 200 day moving average price is $39.83. The company has a market capitalization of $1.03 billion, a PE ratio of 16.56 and a beta of 1.16. 




ScanSource (NASDAQ:SCSC) last announced its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 9th. The industrial products company reported $0.65 earnings per share for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.66 by $0.01. ScanSource had a return on equity of 8.41% and a net margin of 1.79%. The firm had revenue of $813.50 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $833.10 million. During the same period in the previous year, the business posted $0.64 EPS. ScanSource’s revenue for the quarter was up 1.9% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, equities research analysts anticipate that  ScanSource, Inc. will post $2.76 EPS for the current year. 
